Odly I am not excited for christmas at all this year. Well we got our progress report and I got all A's exept a B+. Berkley and Muffin were put to sleep and everyone seems to be ignoring it execpt me. The whole story is well Berkley attacked Muffin on Thursday and had to stay at the vet we were all mad at Berkley I even kicked her because the vet said Muffin might not last the night. The next day I got home and found out my beautiful German Shepard who was only one and had no problems was put down. And the way I had said goodbye to her was kicking her. It was my Moms and Jeffs decision to put her to sleep so they can rot in hell for all I care [sorry I am just expressing how I feel] Then it turns out muffin lived we took her home on saterday. Though she was still very sick. We did not want her to go outside or die alone so we got her a heating blanket on the love seat. But she kept trying to walk away. Sh we put her in Berkleys old cage [whick is preety big} I made all these layers of blankets so she would be comfterble. Later she would not eat so my Mom and I had to force feed her. I had to come in every ten minutes and clean her eye. I also brought her fresh water and brushed her hair. We stayed up til 4 in morning watching this program on how cats used to be gods to ancient Egyptians. Though we did this on sunday and saterday but I hate force feeding her. But she was not cooped up in the cage for the whole time we played with strings. ON monday I stayed home because I was "sick" and watched muffin. My mom took her to the vet that day and said she had puss coming for her mouth and had a broken bone and they had to put her to sleep.
